    "short description": "Digital Video Broadcasting — Terrestrial (DVB-T) is a digital broadcast television format used in Europe and in many other countries in the world.",
    "description": "**Digital Video Broadcasting — Terrestrial (DVB-T)** is a digital broadcast television format used in Europe and in many other countries in the world. Uses COFDM (Coded OFDM, which is OFDM with Forward Error Correction).\nThe adoption of its DVB-T2 extension started in 2010, with additional modes. New receivers are backwards compatible, but older ones cannot support DVB-T2 due to the use of more recent compression standards."
